---
title: Fried Polenta Cakes with Mushroom Gravy and Arugula-Pine Nut Salad
description: Polenta is a tasty alternative to pasta and potatoes. It's made
with cornmeal and typically served either creamy, like mashed
potatoes, or firm. When cooled and firmed, it has a sliceable
texture and can be baked, fried or even grilled!
